:0!important;margin-left:0!important;padding-top:0!important;padding-bottom:0!important;padding-right:0!important;padding-left:0!important; \">","category":"Malvertising","pubDate":"Fri, 17 Nov 2023 17:00:00 GMT","guid":"https://blog.avast.com/avast-threat-report-q3-2023-malvertising","dc:date":"2023-11-17T17:00:00Z","dc:creator":"Avast Threat Labs"},{"title":"AI is fueling a surge in TikTok scams","link":"https://blog.avast.com/ai-is-fueling-a-surge-in-tiktok-scams","description":"<div class=\"hs-featured-image-wrapper\"> \r\n <a href=\"https://blog.avast.com/ai-is-fueling-a-surge-in-tiktok-scams\" title=\"\" class=\"hs-featured-image-link\"> <img src=\"https://blog.avast.com/hubfs/Avast/Press/assets/i/placeholder/Girl-on-phone.jpeg\" alt=\"AI is fueling a surge in TikTok scams\" class=\"hs-featured-image\" style=\"width:auto !important; max-width:50%; float:left; margin:0 15px 15px 0;\"> </a> \r\n</div> \r\n<p><span>TikTok has emerged as a fertile ground for financial scams, specifically those involving cryptocurrency. The platform's wide reach, coupled with its appeal to younger audiences, presents an attractive prospect for malicious actors aiming to exploit unsuspecting users.&nbsp;</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span>&nbsp;</span></p>","content:encoded":"<div class=\"hs-featured-image-wrapper\"> \r\n <a href=\"https://blog.avast.com/ai-is-fueling-a-surge-in-tiktok-scams\" title=\"\" class=\"hs-featured-image-link\"> <img src=\"https://blog.avast.com/hubfs/Avast/Press/assets/i/placeholder/Girl-on-phone.jpeg\" alt=\"AI is fueling a surge in TikTok scams\" class=\"hs-featured-image\" style=\"width:auto !important; max-width:50%; float:left; margin:0 15px 15px 0;\"> </a> \r\n</div> \r\n<p><span>TikTok has emerged as a fertile ground for financial scams, specifically those involving cryptocurrency. The platform's wide reach, coupled with its appeal to younger audiences, presents an attractive prospect for malicious actors aiming to exploit unsuspecting users.&nbsp;</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span>&nbsp;</span></p>  \r\n<img src=\"https://track.hubspot.com/__ptq.gif?a=4650993&amp;k=14&amp;r=https%3A%2F%2Fblog.avast.com%2Fai-is-fueling-a-surge-in-tiktok-scams&amp;bu=https%253A%252F%252Fblog.avast.com&amp;bvt=rss\" alt=\"\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" style=\"min-height:1px!important;width:1px!important;border-width:0!important;margin-top:0!important;margin-bottom:0!important;margin-right:0!important;margin-left:0!important;padding-top:0!important;padding-bottom:0!important;padding-right:0!important;padding-left:0!important; \">","category":"online scam","pubDate":"Wed, 15 Nov 2023 17:00:00 GMT","author":"avastblog@avast.com (Luis Corrons)","guid":"https://blog.avast.com/ai-is-fueling-a-surge-in-tiktok-scams","dc:date":"2023-11-15T17:00:00Z"},{"title":"Fall back...into some good digital health habits","link":"https://blog.avast.com/daylight-savings-good-digital-habits","description":"<div class=\"hs-featured-image-wrapper\"> \r\n <a href=\"https://blog.avast.com/daylight-savings-good-digital-habits\" title=\"\" class=\"hs-featured-image-link\"> <img src=\"https://blog.avast.com/hubfs/fall%20into%20good%20digital%20habits.jpg\" alt=\"Fall back...into some good digital health habits\" class=\"hs-featured-image\" style=\"width:auto !important; max-width:50%; float:left; margin:0 15px 15px 0;\"> </a> \r\n</div> \r\n<p><span>Fall is here, and along with cozy sweaters, family gatherings, and PSLs, comes the tradition of turning the clocks back as Daylight Saving Time (DST) ends. Although we’re not certain why this practice lives on in 2023, it lends itself as a good reminder to check our smoke detectors, flip our mattresses, and even update our digital lives.</span><span>&nbsp;</span></p>","content:encoded":"<div class=\"hs-featured-image-wrapper\"> \r\n <a href=\"https://blog.avast.com/daylight-savings-good-digital-habits\" title=\"\" class=\"hs-featured-image-link\"> <img src=\"https://blog.avast.com/hubfs/fall%20into%20good%20digital%20habits.jpg\" alt=\"Fall back...into some good digital health habits\" class=\"hs-featured-image\" style=\"width:auto !important; max-width:50%; float:left; margin:0 15px 15px 0;\"> </a> \r\n</div> \r\n<p><span>Fall is here, and along with cozy sweaters, family gatherings, and PSLs, comes the tradition of turning the clocks back as Daylight Saving Time (DST) ends. Although we’re not certain why this practice lives on in 2023, it lends itself as a good reminder to check our smoke detectors, flip our mattresses, and even update our digital lives.</span><span>&nbsp;</span></p>  \r\n<img src=\"https://track.hubspot.com/__ptq.gif?a=4650993&amp;k=14&amp;r=https%3A%2F%2Fblog.avast.com%2Fdaylight-savings-good-digital-habits&amp;bu=https%253A%252F%252Fblog.avast.com&amp;bvt=rss\" alt=\"\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" style=\"min-height:1px!important;width:1px!important;border-width:0!important;margin-top:0!important;margin-bottom:0!important;margin-right:0!important;margin-left:0!important;padding-top:0!important;padding-bottom:0!important;padding-right:0!important;padding-left:0!important; \">","category":"Privacy","pubDate":"Tue, 14 Nov 2023 22:13:56 GMT","author":"avastblog@avast.com (Emma McGowan)","guid":"https://blog.avast.com/daylight-savings-good-digital-habits","dc:date":"2023-11-14T22:13:56Z"},{"title":"Who’s most at risk for scams, hacks, and identity theft? (It’s not who you think)","link":"https://blog.avast.com/young-people-at-risk-for-scams","description":"<div class=\"hs-featured-image-wrapper\"> \r\n <a href=\"https://blog.avast.com/young-people-at-risk-for-scams\" title=\"\" class=\"hs-featured-image-link\"> <img src=\"https://blog.avast.com/hubfs/young%20people%20at%20risk%20of%20scams.jpg\" alt=\"Who’s most at risk for scams, hacks, and identity theft? (It’s not who you think)\" class=\"hs-featured-image\" style=\"width:auto !important; max-width:50%; float:left; margin:0 15px 15px 0;\"> </a> \r\n</div> \r\n<p><span>If you asked this question a few years ago, many might have assumed that older generations would be the primary targets of online scams. It makes sense. Most of us view phishing and email scams as clumsy, low-effort routines designed to take advantage of people who simply aren’t as digitally savvy as the younger generation.&nbsp;</span><span>&nbsp;</span></p>","content:encoded":"<div class=\"hs-featured-image-wrapper\"> \r\n <a href=\"https://blog.avast.com/young-people-at-risk-for-scams\" title=\"\" class=\"hs-featured-image-link\"> <img src=\"https://blog.avast.com/hubfs/young%20people%20at%20risk%20of%20scams.jpg\" alt=\"Who’s most at risk for scams, hacks, and identity theft? (It’s not who you think)\" class=\"hs-featured-image\" style=\"width:auto !important; max-width:50%; float:left; margin:0 15px 15px 0;\"> </a> \r\n</div> \r\n<p><span>If you asked this question a few years ago, many might have assumed that older generations would be the primary targets of online scams. It makes sense. Most of us view phishing and email scams as clumsy, low-effort routines designed to take advantage of people who simply aren’t as digitally savvy as the younger generation.&nbsp;</span><span>&nbsp;</span></p>  \r\n<img src=\"https://track.hubspot.com/__ptq.gif?a=4650993&amp;k=14&amp;r=https%3A%2F%2Fblog.avast.com%2Fyoung-people-at-risk-for-scams&amp;bu=https%253A%252F%252Fblog.avast.com&amp;bvt=rss\" alt=\"\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" style=\"min-height:1px!important;width:1px!important;border-width:0!important;margin-top:0!important;margin-bottom:0!important;margin-right:0!important;margin-left:0!important;padding-top:0!important;padding-bottom:0!important;padding-right:0!important;padding-left:0!important; \">","category":"scam","pubDate":"Tue, 31 Oct 2023 09:30:00 GMT","author":"avastblog@avast.com (Emma McGowan)","guid":"https://blog.avast.com/young-people-at-risk-for-scams","dc:date":"2023-10-31T09:30:00Z"},{"title":"This holiday, you could be inviting a fraudster to your home","link":"https://blog.avast.com/family-scams-holiday-seasons","description":"<div class=\"hs-featured-image-wrapper\"> \r\n <a href=\"https://blog.avast.com/family-scams-holiday-seasons\" title=\"\" class=\"hs-featured-image-link\"> <img src=\"https://blog.avast.com/hubfs/seasonal_scams.2.jpg\" alt=\"This holiday, you could be inviting a fraudster to your home\" class=\"hs-featured-image\" style=\"width:auto !important; max-width:50%; float:left; margin:0 15px 15px 0;\"> </a> \r\n</div> \r\n<p><span>As the holiday festivities draw closer, we start to make plans to see the family. Whether you’re a host or a guest, millions will soon gather to catch up, tell stories, watch football, and break bread. Some of us can’t wait, while others are dreading all of the soon-to-be awkward conversations. In some instances, the only thing that could make a family dinner even more messy (besides a food fight) would be knowing someone eating next to you is a scammer, identity thief, or cyber crook. </span><span>&nbsp;</span></p>","content:encoded":"<div class=\"hs-featured-image-wrapper\"> \r\n <a href=\"https://blog.avast.com/family-scams-holiday-seasons\" title=\"\" class=\"hs-featured-image-link\"> <img src=\"https://blog.avast.com/hubfs/seasonal_scams.2.jpg\" alt=\"This holiday, you could be inviting a fraudster to your home\" class=\"hs-featured-image\" style=\"width:auto !important; max-width:50%; float:left; margin:0 15px 15px 0;\"> </a> \r\n</div> \r\n<p><span>As the holiday festivities draw closer, we start to make plans to see the family. Whether you’re a host or a guest, millions will soon gather to catch up, tell stories, watch football, and break bread. Some of us can’t wait, while others are dreading all of the soon-to-be awkward conversations. In some instances, the only thing that could make a family dinner even more messy (besides a food fight) would be knowing someone eating next to you is a scammer, identity thief, or cyber crook. </span><span>&nbsp;</span></p>  \r\n<img src=\"https://track.hubspot.com/__ptq.gif?a=4650993&amp;k=14&amp;r=https%3A%2F%2Fblog.avast.com%2Ffamily-scams-holiday-seasons&amp;bu=https%253A%252F%252Fblog.avast.com&amp;bvt=rss\" alt=\"\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" style=\"min-height:1px!important;width:1px!important;border-width:0!important;margin-top:0!important;margin-bottom:0!important;margin-right:0!important;margin-left:0!important;padding-top:0!important;padding-bottom:0!important;padding-right:0!important;padding-left:0!important; \">","category":"scam","pubDate":"Mon, 30 Oct 2023 09:21:00 GMT","author":"avastblog@avast.com (Emma McGowan)","guid":"https://blog.avast.com/family-scams-holiday-seasons","dc:date":"2023-10-30T09:21:00Z"},{"title":"You know what? Everyone gets a virus now and then.","link":"https://blog.avast.com/everyone-gets-a-virus-now-and-then","description":"<div class=\"hs-featured-image-wrapper\"> \r\n <a href=\"https://blog.avast.com/everyone-gets-a-virus-now-and-then\" title=\"\" class=\"hs-featured-image-link\"> <img src=\"https://blog.avast.com/hubfs/avast-blog/corona-virus.jpg\" alt=\"You know what? Everyone gets a virus now and then.\" class=\"hs-featured-image\" style=\"width:auto !important; max-width:50%; float:left; margin:0 15px 15px 0;\"> </a> \r\n</div> \r\n<p><span>I will never forget the first time I caught a digital bug. I was sitting at my desk at my company’s open-concept office in Chicago when I got an email from HR. It read:</span><span>&nbsp;<br></span><span>&nbsp;<br></span><strong><i><span>Company Policy Reminder: Please Review</span></i></strong><span>&nbsp;<br></span><i><span>Following an incident in the Boston office, all U.S. employees are instructed to review pages 18-21 of </span></i><a href=\"https://www.avast.com/c-website-safety-check-guide\"><i><span>The Employee Handbook</span></i></a><i><span> regarding inter-office relationships.</span></i><span>&nbsp;</span></p>","content:encoded":"<div class=\"hs-featured-image-wrapper\"> \r\n <a href=\"https://blog.avast.com/everyone-gets-a-virus-now-and-then\" title=\"\" class=\"hs-featured-image-link\"> <img src=\"https://blog.avast.com/hubfs/avast-blog/corona-virus.jpg\" alt=\"You know what? Everyone gets a virus now and then.\" class=\"hs-featured-image\" style=\"width:auto !important; max-width:50%; float:left; margin:0 15px 15px 0;\"> </a> \r\n</div> \r\n<p><span>I will never forget the first time I caught a digital bug. I was sitting at my desk at my company’s open-concept office in Chicago when I got an email from HR. It read:</span><span>&nbsp;<br></span><span>&nbsp;<br></span><strong><i><span>Company Policy Reminder: Please Review</span></i></strong><span>&nbsp;<br></span><i><span>Following an incident in the Boston office, all U.S. employees are instructed to review pages 18-21 of </span></i><a href=\"https://www.avast.com/c-website-safety-check-guide\"><i><span>The Employee Handbook</span></i></a><i><span> regarding inter-office relationships.</span></i><span>&nbsp;</span></p>  \r\n<img src=\"https://track.hubspot.com/__ptq.gif?a=4650993&amp;k=14&amp;r=https%3A%2F%2Fblog.avast.com%2Feveryone-gets-a-virus-now-and-then&amp;bu=https%253A%252F%252Fblog.avast.com&amp;bvt=rss\" alt=\"\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" style=\"min-height:1px!important;width:1px!important;border-width:0!important;margin-top:0!important;margin-bottom:0!important;margin-right:0!important;margin-left:0!important;padding-top:0!important;padding-bottom:0!important;padding-right:0!important;padding-left:0!important; \">","category":"scams","pubDate":"Fri, 27 Oct 2023 08:00:00 GMT","author":"avastblog@avast.com (Emma McGowan)","guid":"https://blog.avast.com/everyone-gets-a-virus-now-and-then","dc:date":"2023-10-27T08:00:00Z"},{"title":"What really happens when you get doxxed","link":"https://blog.avast.com/what-really-happens-when-you-get-doxxed","description":"<div class=\"hs-featured-image-wrapper\"> \r\n <a href=\"https://blog.avast.com/what-really-happens-when-you-get-doxxed\" title=\"\" class=\"hs-featured-image-link\"> <img src=\"https://blog.avast.com/hubfs/iphone-low-power-mode-hack.jpg\" alt=\"What really happens when you get doxxed\" class=\"hs-featured-image\" style=\"width:auto !important; max-width:50%; float:left; margin:0 15px 15px 0;\"> </a> \r\n</div> \r\n<p style=\"font-size: 18px;\">So exactly <span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><a href=\"https://www.avast.com/c-what-is-doxxing\">what is doxxing</a></span>? The term can sometimes get misused, so it's important to know what doxxing is–and what doxxing isn't.</p>","content:encoded":"<div class=\"hs-featured-image-wrapper\"> \r\n <a href=\"https://blog.avast.com/what-really-happens-when-you-get-doxxed\" title=\"\" class=\"hs-featured-image-link\"> <img src=\"https://blog.avast.com/hubfs/iphone-low-power-mode-hack.jpg\" alt=\"What really happens when you get doxxed\" class=\"hs-featured-image\" style=\"width:auto !important; max-width:50%; float:left; margin:0 15px 15px 0;\"> </a> \r\n</div> \r\n<p style=\"font-size: 18px;\">So exactly <span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><a href=\"https://www.avast.com/c-what-is-doxxing\">what is doxxing</a></span>? The term can sometimes get misused, so it's important to know what doxxing is–and what doxxing isn't.</p>  \r\n<img src=\"https://track.hubspot.com/__ptq.gif?a=4650993&amp;k=14&amp;r=https%3A%2F%2Fblog.avast.com%2Fwhat-really-happens-when-you-get-doxxed&amp;bu=https%253A%252F%252Fblog.avast.com&amp;bvt=rss\" alt=\"\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" style=\"min-height:1px!important;width:1px!important;border-width:0!important;margin-top:0!important;margin-bottom:0!important;margin-right:0!important;margin-left:0!important;padding-top:0!important;padding-bottom:0!important;padding-right:0!important;padding-left:0!important; \">","category":"Privacy","pubDate":"Wed, 11 Oct 2023 21:17:47 GMT","author":"avastblog@avast.com (Emma McGowan)","guid":"https://blog.avast.com/what-really-happens-when-you-get-doxxed","dc:date":"2023-10-11T21:17:47Z"},{"title":"Your next online dating match might actually be ChatGPT","link":"https://blog.avast.com/your-next-online-dating-match-might-actually-be-chatgpt","description":"<div class=\"hs-featured-image-wrapper\"> \r\n <a href=\"https://blog.avast.com/your-next-online-dating-match-might-actually-be-chatgpt\" title=\"\" class=\"hs-featured-image-link\"> <img src=\"https://blog.avast.com/hubfs/Avast/Press/assets/i/placeholder/Romance_scam.jpeg\" alt=\"Your next online dating match might actually be ChatGPT\" class=\"hs-featured-image\" style=\"width:auto !important; max-width:50%; float:left; margin:0 15px 15px 0;\"> </a> \r\n</div> \r\n<p><span>Ah, the world of online dating! Where else can you find a potential soulmate while lounging in your pajamas? But the realm of online dating, once a straightforward space, has become a complex web of deception: We've uncovered a tool that's been craftily creating deceptive profiles across numerous dating platforms.&nbsp;</span><span>&nbsp;</span></p>","content:encoded":"<div class=\"hs-featured-image-wrapper\"> \r\n <a href=\"https://blog.avast.com/your-next-online-dating-match-might-actually-be-chatgpt\" title=\"\" class=\"hs-featured-image-link\"> <img src=\"https://blog.avast.com/hubfs/Avast/Press/assets/i/placeholder/Romance_scam.jpeg\" alt=\"Your next online dating match might actually be ChatGPT\" class=\"hs-featured-image\" style=\"width:auto !important; max-width:50%; float:left; margin:0 15px 15px 0;\"> </a> \r\n</div> \r\n<p><span>Ah, the world of online dating! Where else can you find a potential soulmate while lounging in your pajamas? But the realm of online dating, once a straightforward space, has become a complex web of deception: We've uncovered a tool that's been craftily creating deceptive profiles across numerous dating platforms.&nbsp;</span><span>&nbsp;</span></p>  \r\n<img src=\"https://track.hubspot.com/__ptq.gif?a=4650993&amp;k=14&amp;r=https%3A%2F%2Fblog.avast.com%2Fyour-next-online-dating-match-might-actually-be-chatgpt&amp;bu=https%253A%252F%252Fblog.avast.com&amp;bv